# Array Elements Print Recursion Variants
# Write a program using your PL to print the array elements using recursion. 

prepare piece of billArray(piece[] of numbers, piece of idx, piece of total){
    check(idx < total){
        bill(tochars(numbers[idx]));

        check(idx < total - 1){
            bill("  ");
        } instead {
            bill("\n");
        }

        billArray(numbers, idx + 1, total);
    }

    serve 0;
}

start(){
    piece of total = 0;
    piece of i = 0;
    piece of value = 0;
    piece[] of numbers = [];

    bill("Input the number of elements to be stored in the array : ");
    total = topiece(take());

    check(total > 0){
        bill("Input " + tochars(total) + " elements in the array :\n");

        pass(i = 0; i += 1; i < total){
            bill("Element - " + tochars(i) + " : ");
            value = topiece(take());
            append(numbers, value);
        }

        bill("The elements in the array are : ");
        billArray(numbers, 0, total);
    } instead {
        bill("Invalid Array Size\n");
    }
}
--end
6
1
2
3
4
5
6
--end
Input the number of elements to be stored in the array : 6
Input 6 elements in the array :
Element - 0 : 1
Element - 1 : 2
Element - 2 : 3
Element - 3 : 4
Element - 4 : 5
Element - 5 : 6
The elements in the array are : 1  2  3  4  5  6